76561198057468437,Not Recommended,402020,23270855,"Posted: 29 May, 2016",all,Just-Korsten,"First off, The Park is not a bad game, it is just not what you expect.Sure, the starting atmosphere is spooky and you get a little bit of a haunted feeling. But there is no follow through. You look for your son in a dark theme park that feels scary and every so often you are interupted by some story your protagonist feels the need to share. Not to say the story is bad, it just doesn't support the game - at least not until you reach the end and it all kinda wraps up.This story telling the game does, negates the whole effect of the dark atmosphere. And soon you will grow complacent in the game. Maybe a jump scare or 2 will startle you, but it never quite feels scary anymore. Quite a shame really.So in the end; don't buy this game if you are looking for a scary or haunting experience. Don't buy it for the story either. Truly the only reason to recommend this game, is if you are fairly new to horror games and want an easy ride."
