76561198080038125,Not Recommended,402020,19847381,"Posted: 22 December, 2015",all,Hexvex,"This ""game"" (more an experience)  should be viewed from 2 perspectives.  First if you are a TSW (mmorpg) player or ex player and second as someone with absolutely no connection to it.As a TSW player:You buy this game to support Funcom, expand your tsw lore knowledge and enjoy one of the more iconic locations from the game in detail.Or to be more honest to get the chipmunk outfit and a ridiculously overpowered P2W talismans that you cant get any other way (which is ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t tbh)Non TSW player:What you have here is 1 maybe 2h walking simulator. There is virtually no interaction to speak of.-Graphics are good enough.-Story is where i would say you will most likely find enjoyment if you like dark psychological horror themes, just dont have high expectations. I did not find it scary, and most scare attempts were made using very obvious and predictable techniques. This resulted in game not feeling creepy or even suspensful.-Performance is not really optimal and some rigs might have issues.-Do not rely on calling out Callum for direction he is a troll, use the maps.-God damn sprint is slow-Near end of game you will be going through the same room and stairs over and over, this is not a bug just annoying as hell.Overall:Would i suggest buying the game at 13 euros. Hell no !    Wait for a deep discount, 4 euros or so at most , unless ofc you need the items for TSW pvp , then well do you really have a choice.Coming as a 3y old TSW player i dare say it is not up to standard.Quality of TSW storytelling and atmosphere upon the games release and first few issues was among the best ever in gaming and certainly in any mmo. Sadly after a rough start the main storyteller and designer Ragnar Tørnquist left and game never really recovered from it. Atm game has a very watered down feeling and this spinoff is a more diluted version of that. Lets hope they do better in the future."
