76561198000712606,Recommended,402020,18720623,"Posted: 27 October, 2015",all,Snarky McSne,"The Park is a horrifying atmospheric adventure game in the same vain of The Vanishing of Ethan Carter and Gone Home.  But I already knew that. What surprised me was the last act of the game when it turned into PT.  I was very pleasantly surprised and probably the most creeped out by that turn of events.I recommend picking up everything you can find.  Notes, photos, articles, the like as that is where the background to the strange going ons of the park is found.  Especially in the last part, a few times, trust me.It stands on its own but if you have played The Secret World you will notice people, places, and events referenced from there like familar old ghostly friends. I'm one of those who had so it made it fun to get mentions to certain motels and diners that feature in TSW. However if you are going in blind it shouldn't be to spoilerific if you want to play TSW after and there is enough background that you will get the jist of the park even if you don't.This is one of those games that it helps to put yourself into the shoes of the character. Hearing her heartfelt pleas especially when she is scared is tragic.  Hearing her ""other side"" or the less sweet motherly side is down right disturbing.  I also liked the themes and dark undertones to the game.  And if you just happen to want to ride the rides of a scary amusement park than this is definetly up your alley.It took me about as long as I thought it would but I HATE missing things so gameplay of the individual will very.  Mine was about 3 hours but if your running through and missing alot it could easily be less than 1 or 2 hours. Or a quicker reader than I am.As to FPS my computer isn't the best so off with the antialiasing and V-snce and a lower setting of screen settings and the lag I get was ignorable at worse and forgettable at best. But that's just my computer and BAD graphics card.Moral of the review: A good game to play when it's dark outside, MUHAHAHAHA."
