76561198000986265,Recommended,402020,18721417,"Posted: 27 October, 2015",all,Raesene,"I played this late at night in the dark with headphones as suggested and it is a pretty dark and spooky game.It's a little slow at the start, especially with the first park ride, but this improves after you get further in. There are some jump scares along the way, but once you become invested in the story I found the anticipation of what was at the end of the journay was what was driving the dark themes of this game.The game is set in Atlantic Island Park, a location from The Secret World. You do not need to have played that game to understand this one, but there are a huge number of references to characters, locations, and events from TSW so someone who has played the MMO will have a different experience from someone who hasn't. Also, there is a companion mission to The Park now live in The Secret World and playing The Park and then The Seven Silences mission enhances the story significantly.The graphics are much improved over The Secret World as The Park uses a different game engine and the game performance was strong. There were some very slight hitches in the gameplay, probably caused by background loading that were noticible. This happened about 4-5 times to me.The sound was great, spooky as expected. The creepy voice on the loudspeakers is a nice touch. You think he is saying something important but no matter how hard you listed you can't quite make out the words.Gameplay was basic as this is pretty much a by the rails game where you follow one path. Left button actives stuff, right button calls out to Callum and also highlights objects you can interact with. Shift sprints. That's about it for controls, very basic but fitting to the game.It's a short game, under 2 hours for me and that's exploring everything. One hint is to read everything you find AND if you revist a location or your perspective of that location changes then read everything again as the stuff you've just read may have changed.I would recommend this game to all TSW players, and you should probably play this before you play Halloween mission in TSW to understand the full story. If you haven't played TSW you can still play this with no issues but you won't understand some of the easter eggs.Rating.7/10 if you haven't played TSW9/10 if you play TSW AND do The Seven Silences mission over Halloween."
