76561198014370185,Recommended,402020,18732015,"Posted: 28 October, 2015",all,Barbarian,"I liked this game and it is thrilling to experience how developers still manage to make good stories. We see the history through the protagonists eyes. Lorraine lost her son a the amusement park and starts searching after him. In the coming sequences we see odd things, experience paranormal things and the context is puzzling. The last scene is surely the climax of the whole story, Lorraines story.As I see it she was not only depressed but seems to have a traumatic story. Just think, early attachment problems, a mother who rejects her and accusing her for having abandoned her by running away with the father. Then father is gone and her relatives dont want to share the insurance amount with her. There she stands alone before she meets a man and happiness is back in her life. But not for so long. The man dies and she becomes a single mother with a low-paId job. She also had post-partum depression for which she also was hospitalized and medicated for. I interpret the park as the conscious level and the grottos and the stairs in the last part as the sub-consciuos levels. As she walk through the rooms several times she relives the trauma again and again. Slowly the repressed memories comes to a consciuos level but she actively tries to repress them. The final scene where she stabs her son seems to me to be a try to get rid of the alien part of the self. I think that her son is in custody and that Lorraine seems to be psychotic.Overall I liked the game as mentioned earlier. There are some cons though. Gameplay is a little bad mechanised and there should have been icons popping up when reading a note and alike. Walking is too slow and I finished the game by running. The game is a little too short and could have been longer.I recommend this game for those who fancy psycology and ambient soundtrack."
76561197999604891,Recommended,402020,18726185,"Posted: 28 October, 2015",all,solendale,"While the game is short and can be completed in less than 2 hours, the story is interesting and the world is very immersive, eerie, and haunting. It's a first person experience game much like Dear Esther and Gone Home or even the Stanley Parable. The game uses a lot of flavor text that the player can find that adds to the background story of the park. This adds to the horror elements which are well done with plenty of scares throughout.That being said the level of interactivity you have with the world is fairly limited although calling out to your son makes for an interesting mechanic. Admittedly, I myself didn't use this mechanic for about the last half of the game as frequently as I did at first. The length was only a con in my opinion due to it leaving me wanting more and curious about The Secret World.I recommend this title to anyone who enjoys an immersive, eerie, paranormal story with a good number of scares."
