,Recommended,402020,34712444,Posted: 3 September,all,Flurry65,"The Park is one of those games that you can finish in like 90 minutes and get your money back for being under the Steam refund hours. However dont speed run the game just for that reason. I really enjoyed the Park for being a really interesting game about how you go completely insane in under 90 minutes of just being there. The graphics are good, the spook's were ok and the storyline felt like there could have been more. I'll list a few things that could really improve this to be a 10/10 game:What is good:- The graphics are on point.- The Park rides felt like they could have been real.- The Music was good to set a creepy tone.- Character design for Chad was great.- The effects of Lorraine going more and more insane is creepy.What could have been worked on:- A longer game: they could have made more rides and make the story way more scary as you go from one ride to the next.- More reading: this is the only way to set the scene is by reading little pages all around the park, super easy to miss and could be the down fall of the player not knowing whats going on.- Shorter rides: The starting ride, tunnel of tales is the longest of the 6 rides (including the house of horrors, but not counting the part where you walk though the clown door.) so you sit there for a good amount of time waiting for the ride to end which is boring, but it turns out you can skip half of the rides and end up just riding the roller coaster, getting the flash light, and beating the game by entering the house of horrors! You just skipped half of the whole story to speed run the game! More rides could have gone in deeper of the true meaning behind the park and could have entered the world a little deeper of Lorriane.- More Scares could have improved the game for being a walking simulator, to a real horror game with not just scares in pieces but all around you, feeling your heart pounding!What needs to be fixed:- so there is a glitch I was having where at the very beginning I had to hold right click to look around and I couldnt get out of the first object I was looking at, so to easily fix this I went into the parks menu and messed around with the mouse settings and fixed it right away. Great first impressions.- I also noticed in some of the cut scenes that my character Lorriane would like flicker a little bit before looking in the direction of the event, this was notice at the scene of the bumper cars with shock Therapy. I guess she was still staring in the direction of what I was looking at before I  clicked the object that triggered the cut scene.- The Story: OK... this one is really messed up but I thought they could have improved on it by a lot and could have built up a little bit more of why was the park haunted in the first place or was it really the whole time. I said I liked the ending but now I go back and think about it, it didn't really make a whole  lot of since to me. You could have missed the whole story line and saw all these random events and be thinking to yourself why is all this happening? I'll tell you something, make sure you read all the pieces of paper found around the park, it will help you understand a little more of what is going on.SO, did I like the game after all I said? Yes, it was a fun game to play for myself. I would give it a 7/10 for graphics and having a really good concept that could have gone futher than  they did. Is it worth the $15? Not really, I bought it for $15's but I would wait till it's on sale just so you dont have to speed run it just for your money back because im stuck with it going almost to 3 hours just to get the whole story. I would say they could of done better with this topic, but we got this... it could have been so much better. But you can see me play it and get my reactions out of it here:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ignn2gW7p14&list=PLiRjZqwT7yMZ7Ko-N3j_bq_MpsXPjFZsdSee for yourself with some real gameplay if you want to pay for it or just watch me get all the hidden things about this game. I hope this review was helpful for you!"
