,Recommended,402020,20782723,"Posted: 27 January, 2016",all,Significant❗🌀,"Disclaimer: This review is opinion based and has been made due to playing the game on my YouTube Channel and is also aimed at other ""Let's Players"". I will also include a rating to whether this game is easy for recording!Hello everyone!My name is SynificHD and I am a YouTuber who uploads many gameplay content, such as this game.This review will show my thoughts and opinions towards the game, also including a link to the game for you guys to check out and hopefully enjoy; and give you an insight of the game!A Park Review:Description:The game ""The Park"" is a first-person walking simulator that isnt much of a survival horror, but is a psychological horror, where you play as a mother who is named Lorraine, who must re-enter The Park to find her lost son; as she explores the horrifying amusement park, she suddenly reveals who she really is, leaving you on the edge of your seat; wondering what the HECK happened!Personal Opinion:""The Park"" has a very basic story line (You're trying to look for your lost son and go through some freaky flashbacks) but holds a very interesting concept being held in what would be known as a ""happy place""; a theme park. The price is also debatable being a somewhat short story but then again the game has a lot of detail in certain parts, especially in sidequests that makes the game more interesting. Overall I could put this game inbetween recommended and not recommended as the game has a few cons but I enjoyed playing and it all depends on your interest.TL;DRI recommend this game to players who enjoy a mind boggeling game, that leaves you questioning its meaning, and for people who enjoy walking simulators that are narrator based, that involves sitting through a lot of dialogue.Easy For Recording?At the time, recording was an issue but it would probably be a lot easier now but I would give this a 7/10 due to long dialogue and trying to cut most of it down into a suitable video.Gameplay Here for Reference ►https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jzcLo1DI4PY"
,Recommended,402020,30825743,Posted: 29 March,all,koral06,"The park is about a mother ,Lorraine, taking her son Calllum to the amusement park. She loses Callum and must search for him around the park.The atmosphere turns dark quickly and a creepy undertone emerges. While Lorrainne is exploring the park there is an interesting backstory as Lorraine hurries to find Callum. The actual gameplay is a walking simulator with no combat or skills required to beat it. It runs almost like a movie, with the ending scenes being my favorite. In general a lot of the park scenes are fantastic, and I enjoyed watching them.One thing many have mentioned is there is little replay value and it is a short game. However, if you're a horror fan like me I think you'll enjoy the atmosphere and storyline."
