,Recommended,402020,18719462,"Posted: 27 October, 2015",all,dhyrup,"An interesting game. I mostly grabbed this because I am a fan of The Secret World MMO, and this game is set within that universe. I appreciated the deeper insight into the the park and its denizens.This is less of a game than an interactive short story... and by interactive, you're really just picking things up and examining them. There is no combat or puzzle solving or any other aspects of a traditional computer game that you may be expecting.That aside, it was fairly creepy... especially with headphones on so you can hear the nuances of the sound effects. It would have been much creepier in the dark, but the sun was still up when I decided to try it out.The only bad things I have to say about it are that it is short (finished it in less than 2 hours) and towards the end, there are elements that repeat over and over. While I know that is there to elicit a psychological effect, I started to get bored of the repetitiveness of it. I also felt the ending was a bit lackluster, but fitting. With the buildup, I guess I was expecting something more dramatic. I was also hoping for more paranormal elements, given the tie in with The Secret World.Anyway, for the price, this game is worth playing if you're a fan of the psychological horror genre, or you're a fan or player of The Secret World MMO. Just try to play it in the dark with headphones on. :)"
