76561198037253620,Recommended,402020,20058554,"Posted: 28 December, 2015",all,Mr. Synth,"First off, if you don't enjoy games like Dear Esther or Gone Home, do NOT get this game, it is a short walking simulator with some horror. now that thats done, I really enjoyed this game, as I do enjoy walking simulators.Pros-story had me interested the whole time-only two or three jumpscares outside of the haunted house, and even then I saw at least one of them coming, rest is pure atmosphere-game is short (took me 1.5 hours to 100% it), but it doesn't overstay it's welcome or start to drag-graphics aren't great, but could be worse, reminds me of Life is Strange-the last section of this game is VERY inspired by PT, it doesn't even try to hide it, I think it worked very well-Chad is really freaking creepy (there is a note on a store window that is chilling about him)-i love the aesthetic of the abandoned and rusted amusement park, and it did feel very real-voice acting is really good and is very effective at showing the slow decline of the characterCons-the text on a lot of the notes is very blurry, most I had to squint at, and some of the hand-written ones i just had to skip all-together-The Bogeyman feels a bit out of place and was not scary at all, though i did still like him-the pop-in was HORRIBLE and in the beginning it is extremely obvious that foliage appeared from nothing, it goes away later on, or i just stopped noticing it-story becomes a bit obvious later on and I pretty much figured it out right away-I think they could have done more with the Chad costume, there is one good use of him early on with him just watching you, I think more things like that with him watching you from from an unreachable place would be effective-Price is a bit much, definitely wait for a sale if you are interested-VERY long load times, however I had a few other games installing in the back so that was probably my fault, there are only 3 load screens i can remember in the entire game, so it 