,Recommended,402020,20349130,"Posted: 6 January, 2016",all,Jabba the Fat,"As a player who decides what games to buy based on the reviews of the certain game, it's my duty to write a complete review about any game i finish, so here is my review:THE PARK:This game is a first person, short, psychological horror, story based walking simulator where you are a mother Lorraine who searches her son Callum throughout the Park, while learning all it's dirty secrets.In this game there is no map, except throughout the Park, and you don't have choices in where you can go, you just go straight ahead and ride the Park's attractions while reading notes while scrolling through the Prak.Before i proceed with the Pros and Cons i would like to remind you that the following are my personal preferences and may differ for any individual who plays the game.PROS:+The story was unique+Whilst a horror game, it isn't always based on scaring you, more like making you think+The world is well designed+The playthrough is pretty simple for new players and experienced ones to enjoy+It has some jumpscares but as many as tehre should beCONS:-It had some fps drops and lags in-game-The characters were bad designed (even though it doesn't really matter in-game)-It was short, like 2 hours playthrough shortSUGGESTIONS FOR DEVELOPERS:-Drop the price a bit, 13€ is too much for a game where no one would play more than 3 hours tops-If you decide to keep the price, make some free expansion parks so that we could experience more Park attractions-Make more games like this, this one was awesomeSUGGESTIONS FOR CUSTOMERS:-Buy it on sale, even though it is worth 13€-Enjoy the full of it in a dark room with your headphones on, trust me, it won't be scary at all ;)-Don't worry about getting all the achievements, almost all of them will be obtained while playing the storyTL;DRThis game is really good and i recomend it to anyone who is into Horror games that are not based on the actual horror but on a good frightening story9/10 keep on Funcom!!!!"
