,Recommended,402020,34460600,Posted: 24 August,all,Azir,"REVIEW MAY CONTAIN PLOT SPOILERSThe Park is a tragic horror game with a very complex, open to interpretation story.In my own interpretation, it shows the struggle of a single, abusive mother with a child after being left by her partner (whom she describes as ""dead"" throughout the game, and might have possibly even killed him in a fit of rage). As her life falls apart, she resorts to prescribed psychotic drugs to cure her depression (to which she becomes addicted), trying to contact one of her very old partners for help and alcohol. Her struggle against self-guilt and trying to justify herself as a good mother and blaming her son and everyone around her for her problems. She eventually breaks down and murders her son (and possibly ex-boyfriend).While this whole video game seems very deep and is a trip showing her life, I think it specifically focuses on an episode of her denying the murder of her son and pretending it never happened, her delusions grow more and more as she tries to wall-off the events of her life on bizarre reasons and fictional things.The ending shows her being questioned by a police man asking her questions about the where-abouts of her missing child.This is my opinion and interpretation of this game's deep and beautifully written story. 10/10."
