,Not Recommended,402020,18794494,"Posted: 31 October, 2015",all,CLiC,"Boring and SLOOOOOOOOOOOOOWGAMEPLAY:The Park is incredibly frustrating to play. The bigest thing is that it takes about an hour and a half to complete the game. However the ACTUAL game is probably only 30 minutes long.This is because when you go to almost any point of interest in the game, the game takes the controls away from you and goes on auto-pilot to deliver mediocre ""scares"" and sub par narration. Never before have I played a game that made me put the controller down for so long.It also has a run button that is removed EVERY time that the player character starts narrating(which is a LOT).The game also likes to mess with your screen Amnesia style. Causing pulsating blurs and worping effects when your supposed to be scared. Alls this does is tell me that the game is begging and assuming me to be scared. When in reality it's actually just annoying and forces your character to walk instead of run, slowing the game down even more.STORY:The game is about as subtle as a sledgehamer to the groin. Right off from the begginng of the game(The Parking Lot) I had guessed the plot of the game.[SPOILTER ALERT]By the parking lot I figured the lady was crazy, by the escalator I figured she killed her kid[END OF SPOILTER]Also there's no clear and present danger to be scared of. I get that is psychological horror, but still that's just stretching the meaning of the word horror. I wasn't scared once during this game. Every jump scare I saw coming, and every possible danger I knew wasn't dangerous because the game took away my controls and went into auto-pilot.Even the big antagonist I wasn't scared of, I actually would run towards this ""threat"" instead of away from it. In fact I thought the antagonist was the best part of the game and wished I saw more of it.FINAL THOUGHTS:The game is not scary, it's not fun to play, I even question calling it a game since most of it just auto-pilot.The game is WAY too short for it's price tag 1 1/2 hours maybe 1/2 an hour if you remove auto-pilot and times when you're forced to walk instead of run.I suspect that this game is nothing more that an advert for Secret World and for players of Secret World to buy this game to see a piece of their MMO in better graphics and of course for the exclusive items you get from buying The Park.Needless to say I do not recommend this game. I have no idea why it has a ""Mostly Positive"" rating on Steam at the time of this review. I suspect that it's just Secret World fan boys freaking out, but this ""game"" isn't worth your time or money."
