,Not Recommended,402020,18723642,"Posted: 28 October, 2015",all,"Sugarcane, God of Rum","2 hours of gameplay. That includes a few minutes to go back and pick up the last 3 achievements that I missed. How is it, you ask? It's okay. It's a creepy setting, there's a few parts that made me flinch a bit. The story is laid out pretty well and the environment tells it alright. But if you haven't figured out the entire plot by the halfway point at the latest, I feel very sorry for you. The ""twist"" was blatantly obvious to me after the first ride and the details about it became almost painful pretty quickly.I have never played The Secret World (the game that this game is pretty much created to promote), so I can't say for certain, but I feel like if I had played TSW, I would have found this game much less appealing. Having no knowledge of Atlantic Island Park or its history at least gave me a lot to explore and learn.I was intrigued by the concept of losing a kid in a creepy, haunted amusement park with waning sanity. Unfortunately, it becomes pretty apparent that your character is entirely unrelatable and unlikable and thus impossible to sympathize with and therefore an immersion breaker. The longer I played, the more I thought that that kid was better off lost in a haunted park than with that awful mother.The most jarring part of the game was the first, I guess... ""jump scare"" or whatever it would be called. And the one that followed was incredibly predictable because of the first and pretty laughable.6/10Atmosphere is good. Story is predictable. Nothing really ""scary,"" just a bit startling occasionally. Obvious Lovecraft inspiration. Notes that should read like a freaked out park goer read more like a badly written H.P. Lovecraft story (maybe on par with one of Lovecraft's childhood stories). Sort, short, short.It's worth it for 10 bucks. Maybe the full price of 13 bucks, too. If you want something to do with an hour or two of your life, there's worse and more expensive ways to spend it. Remember, though: this game was pretty much made for the purpose of promoting The Secret World. It's pretty much an advertisement that you pay $10 to experience. I'm satisfied, but I can certainly see a lot of people walking away disatisfied."
