76561198138455900,Recommended,402020,22870883,"Posted: 8 May, 2016",all,Lrrrrrrr,"Amazing story that captures the feel and atmosphere of The Secret World perfectly, while still maintaining a uniqueness that allows it to stand on it's own. The game is both engagaing and immersive in a way many adventure style games never quite pull off. The sounds of the game are the true gem of the title, with each area of the park pushing ones nervesfurther to the edge with its terrific use of auditory ambience. I often found myself frantically looking around for sources that I never found. It all builds an atmosphere of dread while providing a disturbing kind of soundtrack to the tale unfolding around you. Though short, it's a great game, that remains true to it's source material.My honest opinion is that it's totally worth 10/10As a side note for those who have played The Secret World:The story unfolding in this tale provides depth to one of the most interesting areas on Solomon Island. It will feel familiar and disturbingly alien to those who have ventured into the park before, leaving you with some new questions. The added depth given by the story even provides further insight into discoveries made in the MMO."
