76561198179777631,Recommended,402020,22575904,"Posted: 22 April, 2016",all,lalilulelo,"First things first, I love horror games...however I get scared pretty easily, so this game did freak me out a little. The atmosphere was on point, some jumpscares did get me (I admit a few times I had to pause the game to recover), whereas there were a few towards the end of the game that felt slightly cliched, no spoilers though.Although this is essentially a walking simulator, I felt immersed and loved some of the horror mechanics introduced that weren't just trying to say boo!  Little touches which add to the suspense, things moving very slowly, noticing something out the corner of your eye.  Its small things like this which make the game much more interesting.I was drawn in by the story, which is quite controversial, but I'll say no more.One small issue I had was the drop in frame rate at the beginning of the game, which took away from the immersion.  Had to drop down to high settings which seemed to fix the issue, but felt that it shouldn't have had a problem running on ultra.One thing which I think is important in horror games is the audio, again adding to the atmosphere, the devs got this right.  All the little sounds you hear, the whispering, the protagonists desperation in her voice to find her son, and her reminiscing, all added to the immersion.  Best played with headphones so you can hear everything going on around you.Overall, I would recommend this game when on sale.  I completed the game in 80 minutes.  While it's all about quality and not quantity, some may be disappointed with the content for the price, but if you are after something that's got scares, and an explorative experience, this is great."
,Recommended,402020,18717931,"Posted: 27 October, 2015",all,Sheyon,"It's a short game, as others have said 1-2 hours, but it shines in its story-telling and atmosphere. Those who are familiar with the Secret World MMO will get a kick out of its tie-ins (and there are plenty), though having prior knowledge of TSW is absolutely NOT necessary.That said, I really would like to see more of this sort. Whether you approach this as a standalone product or not, the fleshing out of the game world is fantastic and is worth experiencing at least once. If its length bothers you, catch it on sale. But I have enjoyed Funcom's storytelling -- it is high-quality, creepy, and rich -- and I don't feel like I've wasted my $10 (preorder) at all.I will be returning to the Park."
