,Recommended,402020,18712632,"Posted: 27 October, 2015",all,Zed Clampet,"What a brilliant little horror gem.  It starts with what some may consider a slow burn as it builds up the story, but the horror atmosphere just continued to increase until it was nearly unplayable for me (a great thing in a horror game).  There are a number of jump scares once you get at least half way through, most of them exceedingly well done.  What this does is put you constantly on edge, wondering what are they going to do to me next?The story is quite interesting and takes a dark turn pretty quickly.  It's told to you by the narrator (the playable character) and also by notices and notes that you find.  If you are paying attention, it builds a good sense of mystery which also keeps you on your toes.  The game ends with what seems a P.T. inspired segment that had me in a near panic.The only negative thing I would say about this game is that the letters were hard to read on my laptop.  Other than that, it was one of the best horror experiences I have had on PC.  If you don't mind the short playing time (1.3 hours for me) and love horror like I do, I definitely recommend getting this."
76561198048203286,Recommended,402020,22210608,"Posted: 2 April, 2016",all,sup5577,"watch my video review athttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FRqo2Kg6EyUstoryThe park takes place in the same universe as Funcoms MMORPG the secret world. In this reality all of Earths myths and legends turn out to be true the boogeman is real and his precense is felt in atlantic ilsand ammusement park.You play as  Loraine a single mother who is leaving the park for the day with Her son Callum who realises he lost his teddy bear Mr. Bear. Loraine tells Callum to stay in the car while she checks with the information booth to see if anyone found the bear, Because Loraine does not use child locks on her car Callum runs off into the now deserted amusement park she chases after the little brat and you must explore the now seemingly deserted grounds uncovering its dark history while riding the rides and reading letters lying around.you learn fun facts such as There is a history of children vanishing after dark and grown ups being unable to remember they ever existed. The Park being closed due to a number of unexplainable accidents killing patrons one of whom just so happens to be Callums father. If that was not bad enough their was also that one time the parks mascot Chad the chipmunk gouged out a childs eye with an icepick.presentationVisually the park is hit or miss the scenery of the park itself is very well done the rides look great the atmosphere is unerving and the transition from day to night reminds me of entering otherworld in silent hill. However the character design leaves something to be desired. Loraine looks like a robot and when you enter the haunted house she looks like a robot zombie I have never seen a robot zombie before, but that is what Loraine looks like.The sound is spot on the developers recomend playing with a headset for good reason everything from the rattle of the rollercoaster to docks of the story time boat ride sound steller. The sound team deserves to be applauded.The voicework is also on point the game uses a mechanic where you call out to Callum and he calls back leading you on your journey. I was able to feel Loraine grow more desperate as the night went on. this was a great touch and for a staff of only five voice actors they all gave a great effort.I played the game using a wireless xbox one controller, but it also supports mouse and keyboard. The controls are tight, but limited you move slowly and even when Loraine runs it is as if she is out of breth. you may also interact with objects mainly letters that help to progress the story I should mention some of the letters gave me trouble seing them as the font seemed blurred and as stated earlier you may call for calum.before moving on to the next section it is important that I mention at beginning of the game their is a strange bug that had me restart the game three times before I figured out a fix If you interact with one specific plaque you lose the ability to move This was extra frustrating because it is likely the first item you will interact with and the game tells you to. the fix is to hit escape on the keyboard.  This was the only bug I found on two complete playthroughs but it was annoying.DificultyThe park would best be described as an interactive movie it is not like a traditional survival horror game Loraine is not able to die and there are not really any puzzles to solve outside of slowing rides down so you can get onto them. The hardest part of the game might be finding all of the hidden notes, but due to the parks design being linear it is hard to get lost. When you ride the rides it is just that you are riding a ride you may look around and some creepy things might happen, but it is a passive viewing mode. This does not mean the game is not fun as the story is engaging and the atmosphere is top notch, but the game is about as difficult as drawing a circle as that is the path you take.endingthorughout the game you will see Chad the the killer chipmunk stalking Loraine as well as glimpses of a shadowy figure that is revealed to be the boogeyman. The player learns that Loraine has been on medication and seems to really hate children. In the haunted house she finds Callum on an alter  and with the guidance of the boogeyman kills Callum with an icepick. Earning her the mother of the year awardthe screen fades into Loraine talking with a an investigator who just so happens to be the park attendent she spoke with at the beginning of the game.  she repeats her opening monologue as if she is reliving the horrible memories in her shattered mind. The moral of the story is if your mother tells you to stay in the car you better listen or she will hunt you down kill you with an ice pick.bonus contentThe park has a few unlockables. First there are 14 achievments that you may earn while playing. Most are unlocked just by simply riding the rides and exploring the park. Unfortiatly you will not get anything extra for earning all achievments there are also 6 steam trading cards based on the parks rides you can only get 3 for playing the game forcing you to trade with others to complete the set.The final peice of bonus content I could not take advantage of because it requires that you have a seceret worlds account. If  you do  have an account  it unlocks a Chad the chipmunk costume as well as receiveing 3 legendary talismans 1 for healer, tank, . This is a neat nod to the players of the secret world, but since I do not play that game I have no idea if they are any good.I do wish there was something extra to unlock for completing the game maybe the option to dress up loraine as Chad the chipmunk on your next playthrough as it stands outside of maybe earning a missed achievement there is very little reason to replay the game.final verdictThe park is very short it took me under two hours to beat.The game is linear with little room for exploration best described as an interactive movie. The tension slowly ramps and the last thirty minutes is almost worth the price of admission alone the game has dropped from $20 dollars to $12.99 on steam if you own the secret world this game will unlock some extra perks so if you enjoy creepy games and don't mind jump scares I would say it is worth a play"
,Recommended,402020,18736358,"Posted: 28 October, 2015",all,SavingPrincess,"First things first.If you have never heard of or played The Secret World, you will not really ""get"" this game.  Most of the game will seem arbitrary, dissonant in tone, and nonsensical.However, if you understand where ""Kingsmouth"" is, have completed ""The Seven Silences"" quest and know who Carrie Killian is... this game is fantastic and chances are, you've already bought it.I can't outright recommend this game otherwise, you probably won't enjoy it.  There aren't enough ""jump-scares"" to fill a proper ""watch me shriek"" YouTube ""let's play,"" and a lot of the story is delivered through inner monologue and visual imagery that won't make much sense to you without the greater context.I'm giving this a thumbs-up however, because if you love The Secret World and Tørnquist's unique neo-Cthulhu stylings, then you'll get exactly what was intended out of this game."
