,Recommended,402020,18839233,"Posted: 2 November, 2015",all,Sunny,"The Park is a truly fantastic narrative experience. It's tense, atmospheric, and well-written. I was engrossed. Definitely a ""set the atmosphere"" kind of night. Turn off the lights, stick on your headphones, and get lost in the story. It's been a while since a game left me completely unnerved with a deep sense of dread.There seem to be some misconceptions about what The Park is. You do not have to have played The Secret World. While there are nods here and there and a shared universe, The Park is a standalone experience. There's a lot to appreciate here as a TSW fan, but it's mostly in the way of ""this is already thematically something you enjoy"".This is also a game in the loosest sense. It's a narrative experience, an interactive short story. The price-point is appropriate for what you are getting. I pay the same for a movie, and it shares a similar length. There's no combat, no puzzles, and limited interactivity.If you enjoy a quiet kind of horror that crawls under your skin and leaves you dreading what's behind the door... not because it could kill you... but because the idea of it is so much worse than any reality, because the thought of opening that door and seeing that living room again makes you hold your breath... The Park is for you. I couldn't have asked for a better way to spend my post-Halloween horror wind down."
