76561198165413952,Recommended,402020,18876931,"Posted: 4 November, 2015",all,hotsodajerk,"I've read the good and the bad reviews, and ultimately a game like 'The Park' will be polarizing. On one hand the story, being widely open to interpretation, will leave some unsatisfied and wanting a clearer explanation. On the other hand, there are those like me who don't mind filling in the blanks with my imagination and taking in the atmosphere.The game, for the most part, falls just short of scary, the focus being more on the the protagonist's increasing panic at the thought of losing her child than the cheap jump scares and monsters we're so used to encountering in modern horror titles. It is a descent into horror rather than a trip through it. It starts 'Ether One,' takes a turn into a 'Silent Hill' atmosphere, then makes a very smooth transition to the psychological horrors of titles such as 'PT' and 'Layers of Fear.'I loved this game. It was just the right length to match the pacing of the increased intensity and it left me wanting more. I will definitely be trying out TSW now, knowing that this game weaves into the lore of that title.One issue and it seems to be a common one. I had huge frame rate problems on any settings above high with 2X AA. That seems to be the magic combination of settings in case anyone else is having these issues."
