76561198032542687,Recommended,402020,18804210,"Posted: 31 October, 2015",all,darxide23,"I'll start off by saying that I'm a huge fan of The Secret World and generally enjoy the work that Funcome does. I have my issues with Funcom and they way they have handled things historically, but my opinion of them remains overall positive.Overall, I recommend this game to anyone who likes psychological horror games like Silent Hill and/or modern atmospheric story telling games like Gone Home or The Vanishing of Ethan Carter. If I were to give it a numbered rating I would give it a 7.5 or 8 out of 10. Pretty good, but not without it's flaws.A lot may think that a 7.5 out of 10 is too high for what this game is, but I argue that the game did not try to be more than it was and we all knew the game was merely a story telling medium. An interactive movie if you will. At right around two hours, this is a pretty accurate description.The developers got the atmosphere right. It begins shortly after the game starts and doesn't let up. You go from ride to ride in The Park while the protagonist gives some exposition in between. This breaks up the tension nicely without completely ruining it, although I feel like there were just too many points where the suspense that had been so masterfully built up was not capitalized upon. I get that buildup of tension just to have it turn out to be a ""false alarm"" is something horror movies do on the regular, but The Park abuses this too much. When the scares finally do happen, they don't feel quite as intense as they could. You're more relieved that they finally happened and it wasn't another empty build up.There are references gallore to the people, places, and lore of Solomon Island that players of The Secret World will love. I know I did. They are seemlessly integrated into the game world, though. They aren't obvious fan service and anybody who has never played The Secret World should not feel lost or feel like they are missing something. It was all done very organically.Finally, there's the bit about the ending. Without spoilers, I will have to say that I'm most disappointed in the ending of the game. There was too little resolution, too many unanswered questions. Unanswered questions are the bread and butter of this type of game, but there were just too many of them. It almost feels like none of the loose threads were tied up at the end so instead of an intreaging mystery, you're left with a tattered tapestry that is unraveling around itself. This is especially disappointing since Funcom's main strength is story telling and the game directory, Joel Bylos, is usually extremely strong in this respect. I feel that this might have been the result of the game not being intended for public release when they began working on it. It started as a learning project for Funcom to learn the Unreal Engine. Mabye I'm off in my assumption, but that's how it feels. This is where the game lost most of the points and leads me to give it a 7.5 out of 10.tl;dr: It was worth the experience, but could have been so much more."
,Recommended,402020,18806088,"Posted: 31 October, 2015",all,Roundaround,"Great game for those looking for a spook and can't handle the fast-paced chase games like Outlast and The Evil Within.  Quite short, but tells a very well executed story that leaves you breathless.  A definite recommendation."
,Recommended,402020,21972289,"Posted: 21 March, 2016",all,Typhoon Jim,"Fun, but very flawed. Serious pacing and structure issues in the first half, however the literal descent of the second half was well done.I actually thought knowledge of TSW detracted from the experience. Turned some moments that might have been scary into ""Oh, it's *that* guy. Hello, That Guy, I beat the hell out of you with fist knives a while back. You drop terrible gear now, so I won't be seeing you again.""Grab it when it's on some extreme sale, if the idea of a 5 dollar an hour game bothers you. I for one think the world could use more games of about this length and hope Funcom refines their design. They are on the right track, just not arrived yet. Overall, an aspirational 6/10."
