76561198064149112,Recommended,402020,18825416,"Posted: 1 November, 2015",all,TK29,"I’ve always thought things like urban exploring were super cool. I used to work for a certain media giant and its theme parks and exploring the abandoned and left to rot secrets there were some of the most thrilling experiences I’ve had in my life. So when I started seeing The Park in my recommended titles I knew it was for me. A horror walking simulator in an abandoned theme park? Sounds awesome. I have never played or even heard of The Secret World prior to playing this.The Park creates an awesome atmosphere through great graphics and narrative story telling. The narration is well voice acted and the monologue does well progressing the story. Each ride felt pretty real and I loved that they weren’t cut scenes and that you had full control of the camera on each ride. The climax of the game was super creepy and really tense. The way the notes are scattered and written is great too. If you take the time to read them you’ll have some idea what’s going on. If you don’t read any of them you’ll have no idea what’s happening. I like that in this type of game. It provides incentive. At the end of the game I was really enjoying myself. I was creeped out and trying to piece together what exactly was going on. Then, sadly, they completely ruined the atmosphere that they had set up and ended the game with a third person cut scene. They give you full control over your character for the entire game and then take it away from you for the ending. I have no idea why someone thought that was a good idea. Yes the game is short, but it isn’t a full retail priced game and the atmosphere is great. Gamers need to stop being brats and expecting 50 hour games for $10. I was definitely willing to purchase additional content for the game, to get more of a picture of what was going on and I was sort of hoping that there would be additional content to do that, but after the ending I’m hesitant and kind of turned off to the story. I enjoyed the game, it’s a good buy for $10 especially since I played through most of it on Halloween but the ending leaves a very bad taste in my mouth.I’ll probably play through one more time to really soak in the atmosphere and get the achievements that I missed but I probably won’t touch it again otherwise. Other horror games like this have been known to follow up with free updates with additional content or maybe even a reasonably priced expansion. Those might get me to come back for another couple of hours but otherwise this is a 10ish dollar one time play through experience. Get it for $10 instead of renting an HD horror movie. Sort of recommend."
