,Recommended,402020,33548393,Posted: 14 July,all,Tak Blue,"Disclaimer: If you want to be scared constantly and have a fear of character death, this game is not for you.Proclaimer: If you want to enjoy a fantastic, haunting, deeply emotional story, this game is for you.I'll do my best not to drop any spoilers in this review. If you enjoyed What Remains of Edith Fitch, or The Secret World, or both; you will certainly love this game. It is a NARRATIVE game which is clearly said by the devs in the very first video on Steam. This should express to you that this game is about the story, and not a challenge. I feel that many of the negative reviews are based upon the fact that the buyers expected a jump-scare, chase-escape ridden Horror game. This is not that kind of game, and should not be advertised as such. This is like watching a scary cartoon only the subject matters are very real and haunting.The plot? Well, lets just say they leave a lot open to interpretation and it's a good thing. You should be free to draw whichever conclussion you think best fits from this game and it's ending.Play: Its point and click. However I do appreciate that the devs allow a run function while in the park. I do not enjoy a constant pace game which drags. This game allows you to follow what is an EXTREMELY linear path, but at your own pace. The prompted narratives are well placed and reminded me a lot of Edith Finch, which is an absolutely amazing game. Do not expect to play this game, just let it play and help it along yourself by reading the extra little notes along the way.The Ugly: This game is not designed to be re-playable immediately. It's like a Movie, you watch it, you forget it, you think about it, you watch it again.Personal: Without spoiling too much, this game does deal with concepts of psychological disorders in a very in-your-face manner. As a veteran with severe PTSD which causes depression and anxiety I greatly appreciated the fact that they do their best to show people how terrible of an experience it is to go into recovery.8/10"
