,Recommended,402020,18755193,"Posted: 29 October, 2015",all,Law,"I've said ""Yes"", but it's more of a ""maybe"". I did enjoy the park. I would recommend it to othersifthey like these walkabout games.**99% Spoiler Free**The Cons:There isn't a list or inventory of collected notes. This makes it possible to miss notes without even realising you've missed any, which can lead into the ending being quite confusing/nonsensical. Mind you, it felt like I found every note (only found one extra on the second playthrough), and the ending still raised questions. It would definitely feel more confusing had I missed a lot of the notes. It's not a hard thing to do, and if Funcom make another game like this I would love for it to be included, so that I know I've definitely read everything.The character development. The main character is portrayed negatively very early, and the ending more or less falls flat because of it.It's a slow, slow, rollercoaster. Every person will more or less have the exact same experience. One person may find a note or two the other person didn't, but there is at least one note the game forces you to read before allowing you to progress. I understand that there is a fine line between threatening the player and frustrating them, but there just aren't any threats, which removes most of the suspense. At one point the game tried to force suspense down my throat by murdering a violin.The notes. Specifically, the fonts and sizing. At 1080p I had a hard time reading some of the notes, either the font felt too small, or the handwriting was hard to understand. The handwritten notes were a nice touch, but it would be nice if the text on them was a little bigger. The font on the typewritten note was a little hard for me to read in places. I don't have dyslexia, so it's not that I need everything in comic sans.The pros:It's enjoyable, despite the issues I have with the game. The first playthrough can be quite enjoyable, but after that the only reason to do a second playthrough would be if you felt you'd missed some notes, which is a feeling you might have after the ending. However, I would recommend playing it a second time directly after seeing the ending, at least the first part.It ties in well to their established world, and while I have issues with how the character is portrayed and how some of the information is conveyed, it's enjoyable."
