,Recommended,402020,18829463,"Posted: 1 November, 2015",all,English Muffin,"When I first watched the trailer for this game I was really afraid it was just going to be another ""run for your life"" horror game.  After actually playing it, I’m actually happy to say it was not.  While I’m not saying it was perfect, this game definitely left me feeling super creeped out (there were a few times I just wanted to say “fork that child and his disturbing responses”).  I got a serious Silent Hill vibe at times with the eerie music, the incoherent voices over the PA, and jump scare moments where you knew they were going to happen and they still made you jump.Best part of this game is the semi-PT-ish elements in the Haunted House.  There were seriously moments down there that I really didn’t want to progress fearing less what they did and more what I thought they were going to do.My only complaint is that the game felt a little too short and the story left me a bit more confused about some elements than I would have liked.Still trying to understand the fly in the jar..."
,Recommended,402020,18831497,"Posted: 1 November, 2015",all,TheSkyCapt,"The Park is a psychological horror game that is set inside a seemingly abandoned theme park. The game is primarily story based with the player guiding a mother through the park, interacting with the various rides in order to find her son who is lost somewhere within the park.The game excellently sets it's tone early on in the game and the creepy atmosphere is coupled with the eerie nature of the mother as she narrates her backstory as the game progresses.Control wise, The Park is very similar to many first person horror games, such as Amnesia, Among the Sleep, etc. Move with the WASD keys, shift to run, left click to interact. There is no map to show you where you are going as the game encourages exploration. To find your way, the player presses the right mouse button to call for your son, in which your son will respond from the direction you are to go. While helping to build the creepy atmosphere, this mechanic can get a little confusing at times as you are not quite certain where the voice is coming from. This can be fixed in the options menu with a setting to provide a directional guideline along with the vocal response.The Park's stpry is told through a mix of narration and notes hidden around the park. The narration tells the story of the player character, Lorraine, and her son. The notes reveal the dark history behind the Solomon Island Park, both methods offer quite the unnerving experience as the story plays out, building to confrontations with the park owners and the mysterious man in a mascot suit.While the Park does sell itself very well, the price of $12.99USD is a bit steep as I was able to finish the game in under an hour, I was able to get it during the Halloween sale for cheaper, so I recommend this game, but maybe when the price is dropped."
76561198074382973,Recommended,402020,18839021,"Posted: 2 November, 2015",all,Gledam_U_Zvijezde,"The Park is not game it is interactive movie with minor interactions .Yes !  I recommended this to TSW players ,there are some connections with 2015 halloween mission ; Seven Silences ! enjoy"
