,Recommended,402020,18846918,"Posted: 2 November, 2015",all,Lumi,"The Park is short, moody, thought provoking and overall atmospheric little game.Developed by Funcom in couple month as a spin off - tale for their sublime MMO, The Secret World, it mostly does offer a fascinating peek for the players of the multiplayer game, but also serves as intriguing standalone piece for the newcomers.It's not the most scariest, or most thought provoking game, but with night time, lights off and headphones on, you can get a damn nice trip for few hours into a amusement park that packs a good share of thrills and rides!Only gripe I really can think of, well, outside of feeling at points a bit rushed (which is understandable considering what pace this was developed), is that while the little lore shoutouts and easter eggs are definetly nice touch for the existing fanbase, some of them can really puzzle out the newcomers and there ain't really much answers unless you're going to take a plunge into their MMO - and in that sense I think this actually works as kinda interesting first taste to get involved with the game!I like Funcom's new approach and I wouldn't mind seeing more games like these in future. Nice!"
