,Not Recommended,402020,18718558,"Posted: 27 October, 2015",all,jake,"ok..so this gamei haven't ever been mad at a game just for being the game that it is beforei've been mad at bad gameplay, but never anything like thisthe park is a ""horror/explorative adventure game"", which really just means its a horror game with no combat/health/ai/actual danger, which instantly takes all of the impact out of any real scares the game could have. Because of this it focuses completely on small jump scares. The game is less than 2 hours long (more about this later) and there's literally about 4 jumpscares and thats the entire horror aspect of the gameyou'd think that since there are zero quality scares in this horror/adventure game it would be more about the adventure and the amazing cinematic story right? i thought so too, but the thing about this game..from the first announcement they said the game was only meant to be an hour or two long, so i'm really confused about how the planning for this story went. The gameplay is literally walking around between cutscenes reading occasional letters on the ground that don't really form a complete story anyway, and the ""twist"" is predictable within the first 5 minutes of the game or maybe even in the trailers.-This game, in its short time, uses every horror stereotype/cliche known to man and completely ruins all of them..i cant go into much detail without spoiling the ""story"" though.-the first 30 minutes of the 2 hour game are just riding amusement park rides. (its spooky because you're the only one on the ride! ooooh!)-There are 5 characters in this game and only 1 of them has a single shred of personality and it's totally ripped apart, changed and ruined by the end of the game although there was barely anything there to start with.-You get no time with the kid before he goes missing so you have no emotional bond or reason to actually want to find him-the mother is the only character in this game with more than 2 lines unless you count the kid's prerecorded whisper when you press the mouse button to yell for him-there is SO MUCH unexplained in backstory and lore, but the main story is so uninteresting that by the time the game's over you dont care about what you missed-it tries to copy the repeating hallways trick from things that did it amazingly like PT but completely ruins it..without any real scares this is just repetitive busywork to extend the game's already short playtimeOverall The Park was a game i was originally very excited for from the first trailers, but was extremely dissapointed with the bad voice acting, short underdeveloped story, boring characters, weird mechanics, and lack of actual horrorTL;DR 1/10 cuz i got to ride a rollercoaster, thank god for steam refunds"
,Not Recommended,402020,18717810,"Posted: 27 October, 2015",all,Usmovers_02,"MehNot a good horror game, not a bad horror game. Just not much here at all. The scares don't really start until you've basically left the actual park. The park itself has nearly no scares of any variety. There's maybe 3 or 4 jump scares, some decent psychological scares (but only at the very end when you're not really in the park). It's got a pretty eerie atmosphere though.Controls are clunky and slow and unintuitive. The shout mechanic is literally just a waypoint marker.The story is decent given how very short the game is. I care just enough about the mother to want to know what's going to happen and the newspaper clippings really give the park a chilling history. Too bad the park itself doesn't take advantage of ANY of it's back story. Unfortunately the game kinda just... ends. No emotion from the final scene. Length is also a serious problem. Taking my sweet time I managed to beat the game in 1.5 hours. There's nothing to explore and the very short story is severely drawn out by slow movement speed and even slower mandatory rides. There's less substance here than your typical Saw or Paranormal sequel.Graphics are decent but performance is meh at best. Given the lack of draw distance, high res textures or overly detailed objects I'd expect to be able to max 60 this game at 5760x1080 with my computer (GTX 980Ti, Intel Core i7 4790k) but even with reduced settings could only get about 40-50 frames. Hardly terrible numbers at all. No serious dips and no choppiness. The graphics themselves are very decent. They more than do the job and don't detract from the game. The occasional animations however do detract from the game. They're simply bad but fortunately there aren't many animations at all. Also the triple screen support is quite excellent I'm happy to say. I didn't have to do any tinkering to get it to work and there is nearly zero screen warp on the outer edges.Overall I cannot recommend this game. Though it's not bad it excels at absolutely nothing including being scary. I won't even say I was disappointed by the game as it has decent moments. Do I regret my 10$ purchase? I don't. But Layers of Fear is a substantially better game in every way for about the same price. Basically this game feels like the lead up to the very first real scare of a full blown horror game.EDIT: Honestly no idea why people are saying this review isn't helpful. There's a difference between disagreeing with something and thinking it isn't helpful but... I guess this is the internet we're talking about here. Would welcome comments on how to improve the review or why people disagree."
