,Not Recommended,402020,18718675,"Posted: 27 October, 2015",all,Thomas the Tank Engine,"This game has to be one of the biggest let downs for me this year for the indie horror scene. We have all seen our fair shares of terrible indie horror games on Steam but this one was just so promising.This game is wildly short, in all honestly you can finish it in about 1 hour and still get the full message the game is trying to convey. Don't get me wrong this game has some really awesome parts to it that makes it stand out, such as its creepy setting, art style, and beautiful visual fidelity from the Unreal Engine 4.I will give it to the art designers, they did a wonderful job but fell really short.This game puts you in the shoes of a mother who has lost her child in a theme park, you must find him as you physologically unravel the mother's mind. This sounds like a good idea, and honestly delievers in some aspects, but in the strongest points it falls so short that it hurts.In this game you will experiance four slow moving boring rides, with little to no personality. It is a damn shame since the art team did such a great job at the park's design itself. In a spooky carnival maybe you should of put more creepy physological design into it, and turned the speed up a bit more. Every ride in this game is a choir. Yes, a literal chore.I found the acting actually quite good for a small indie team, and it delievers great on that part! I loved the mother's role as she gets more and more insane as the game progresses. That being said, she really is the only actor in the entire game, so good job nontheless.The main villian you meet in this game has a really sweet design too! I love how he looks, just so creepy and well thought out. I very much enjoy this aspect.Also what about that horror part? Is it spooky? Will it make it hard to sleep after this game?!?!? The short and easy answer is no. I wouldn't even call it a horror game, as it only has about 2 jump scares that even work and nothing phsycologically hit me. Such a sad, and dissapointing aspect.If this game was longer I believe it could of been passable, but with its boring and lack of personality rides, bland story, and overall lack of creepy design I have to say I don't reccomend it but like what it was trying to be. Maybe if they spent more time on it and tried harder, they would of had a great game and experiance on their hands."
