,Recommended,402020,21866974,"Posted: 16 March, 2016",all,Rinera,"It's a great treat for The Secret World players, but probably not from the perspective of somebody that knows nothing about the park and the story behind it from the game.-The rest of this is probably full of indirect spoilers. You were warned!First of all, I've heard complains about how the game is just cheap jumpscares, but that is not true at all. The game provides a proper psychological-horror experience if you play by its rules and follow the instructions it provides instantly and linear path it clearly puts you into. I was wondering what's really going on during my trip in the park and why I am seeing what I see. It's mostly an interactive story, a walking simulator, but it's a well delivered story.The problem with the story though is that even during the events and the rides, you get very little background as to what is really going on, mostly in the form of boring newspapper and general papper cutouts. That leaves those that know nothing about the park in TSW in the black. There are also monologues by the main character throughout the game that help provide a background, but while it helps understand the main character, it doesn't help understand the world you are in.Graphically wise, the game looks great. It provides a ""spooky"" atmosphere and combining that with some weird events that happen gives you the feeling that you are not really safe even if you know you are. Funcom has never really failed to deliver on that department, so it doesn't surprise me!There are a few issues though, like some events needing more... oomph so to speak. Some things appearing and disappearing in a very cheap way and the mouths having light in them for some reason, making it always look weird. Nothing too major though, just nitpicking.Yeah, I do recommend this interactive story. It's good if you are into this sort of experiences. However, if you haven't played TSW and don't feel like going through some in-game reading then you probably can skip it. If you are really out of horror games to play and you are looking for anything, it's good enough!"
