,Recommended,402020,24190373,"Posted: 8 July, 2016",all,Djevel,"To address the elephant in the room...it's very short. Maybe 2hrs of gameplay, if you take your time and enjoy the scenary. As a The Secret World (TSW) player, The Park was kind of a given to play. As a TSW player, you'll easily recognize the main attractions of the park, however, the walkthrough of it all doesn't visually match up with TSW. It's much more expansive, meaning it takes a bit of time to walk from one attraction to another, picking up the pieces of the story (as well as the needed equipment to progress that storyline) until you eventually complete the narrative. It's less a game than than an interactive story. No puzzles, combat, etc. It's not scary, though some portions are suspenseful. The sound and voice acting are pretty top notch, though. In similar vein to TSW, the ambience of the place is worth it all. I bought this on steam summer sale @ $6, so I'd say it's probably worth it for that. For the $12 asking price...that's a little steep. It's really a one time play through just for the story, maybe a second if you are attempting all the achievements."
