,Recommended,402020,22648639,"Posted: 26 April, 2016",all,undrentide,"Short and SweetNever heard of Secret World before of which The Park is a spin off. Turns out i didnt really need to. This is a story intesive walking simulator for all intents and purposes and one which does its job very well. The story is about a woman and her son who is about to leave a theme park just as its closing. The son realises hes lost his favourite teddybear somewhere in the park and the woman goes to inquire with reception about finding said bear. In the meantime hotheaded son sneaks into the park to look for the bear and what essentially follows is a game of cat and mouse.The Park has its own character and is dark and brooding with more than a hint of the supernatural...the story unfolds and for anyone who played Konami's P.T demo this game will definately resonate.Yes its short, i finished it in a couple of hours, but in those two hours i sat fully immersed with the lights off and headphones on and had quite a few jumps.If you see this in the sales, and want a brief diversion from lengthier games id recommend it. Not quite worth full price though as its not a game that really benefits from a repeat runthrough unless your showing off the park to a friend.The developers could make a good full sized game from this!"
