,Recommended,402020,23812580,"Posted: 25 June, 2016",all,I Jedi,"I don't believe that The Park is in the same arena as other mystery games such as The Vanishing of Ethan Carter, but it does a good job of keeping the player engaged in the story, that the adventure is worth the price. In this game, you won't find yourself shooting bad guys, killing monsters or doing much of anything else except solving the mystery surrounding Atlantic Island Park and more so Lorraine's son, Callum, and his disappearance.The visuals are great but not amazing, the mechanics are solid, and if you can use WASD on your keyboard, you're 90% of the way to learning how to interact in this game. The biggest complaint I have is that the story is rather short - I finished it in a little over an hour and a half, but the story is definitely something one will want to experience for themselves. Overall, if you liked The Vanishing of Ethan Carter, this game is sure to deliver a good experience, too."
