76561198207765791,Recommended,402020,28090773,"Posted: 29 November, 2016",all,alisoncircus,"This is not a game. It's a story. It is marginally interactive in that you need to respond to keep moving forward, and it nominally has choices - but there's only one choice that will continue the story, so once you've moved around it until you've seen all the scenery, you go back and do what it asked you to do in the first place.Don't get me wrong - it's a very good story. Quite absorbing, and you're not certain of the ending until you actually get there. I enjoyed the two hours that it took me to finish it - although I could have done it in less if I hadn't looked at all the scenery. It's good, very good. But it's not a game. As long as you know that, and know that it's merely an evening's entertainment, you can decide if the price was worth it. I got it on sale for Halloween, and I'm satisfied. So I recommend it - for anyone who wants a good story."
