,Recommended,402020,30100560,Posted: 22 February,all,Citizen_Pain,"THE PARK - A Review by Citizen_PainForewordThis Review ofThe Parkis the first in, what i hope to achieve, a line of reviews giving detailed information about the game from not only my perspective, but i'll even try to stay close to the facts and just add my personal opinion in through small doses. I'll also try to steer clear of spoilers and not ruin the fun for anybody, but if you aim to play the game without any information on story or gameplay whatsoever, try it out yourself and don't read on. I'm a german native, so excuse any and all shortcomings when it comes to the english language.Short OverviewSingle-player gameFirst person viewHorror gameSteam Trading Cards and AchievementsDeveloped by FuncomLore tied into „The Secret World“ by FuncomExclusive items for use in „The Secret World“ upon purchaseWhat isThe Park?The Parkis a single-player, first person horror game, currently sold in a price range of under 15 bucks. It is sarcastically labeled as a walking simulator and, while i don't support the mockery that comes with it, not entirely unjustified. The Park aims to deliver you a story. It does not want to show off crazy mechanics, breathtaking graphics or intriguing gameplay. It is just a story. Seeing that the Developer of the game isFuncom, you can expect a good story though. The best way to describe this game is not as a game, but as a movie. You pay for the narrative, but this time it's you being in the drivers seat and exploring the story yourself instead of being told the narrative by movie characters. If you are looking for a game with great replayability or casual gameplay,The Parkis not for you.The game itselfThe game puts you into the perspective of Lorraine, a seemingly single mother, who took her son, Callum, to an amusement park calledAtlantic Island Park. The game does not give you many explanations or an introduction, it just lets you jump right in. You find yourself in the parking lot with your son in the backseat of your car. Shortly after, you are being told that your son has run back into the park after it has closed, and you, being a good mother, run after him. From there, it all goes to worse. The goal of the game, as you are told, is to find your son, Callum.You will soon find out though that there is way more to it than that. The game forces you to not only explore the past of the suddenly not so happy and fun amusement park, but also Lorraines past and her relationship with her son, Callum. „Find your son“ quickly turns into „find out what happened“.The game delivers it's story to you via clever monologue of Lorraine while you steer her through the park and let her ride the various rides and attractions. The narrative just adds to the creepy and weird atmosphere at the park, and while seeming spooky, but not scary in the beginning, as you progress, more and more jumpscares are woven into the gameplay as the narration takes dark and twisty turns. The lore of the game, especially the location being the Atlantic Island Park, is a nod to Funcoms popular MMORPG „The Secret World“, the park being a location there and some characters from the MMORPG appearing in „The Park“ as well. Furthermore, the game has one or two missable side-stories tied in, and delivers some background through notes and letters scattered throughout the park. The gameplay is described pretty easy: You walk and interact with things in the park. There are just two buttons outside of your movement, one to interact with highlighted objects, one to shout for Callum. Everything that happens at the park has an effect on Lorraine, not only through her voice in the narrative and how she yells after her son, but through visual and aubile effects on screen, the vision becoming blurry and your heart rate becoming louder as Lorraine gets scared.What makes this game greatThe story is on point with this game. If you love games with a good narrative, you will absolutely dig „The Park“. The atmosphere is beautiful, the imagery, even though simply designed, can let you stop in your tracks and just wonder, if you really want to go there. Lorraines monologues are perfectly tied in to your exploration of the park and herself, triggered as you walk over certain points in the map. The haunting scenery makes for an adventure, and while linear, it forces you to reflect on some things you've heard or seen.  For what „The Park“ wants to deliver, it does so with ease and to a certain point even perfect. Players who already enjoyed „The Secret World“ will have a bonus coming into this game, not only because of the already known locations and characters, but because it is just pure amazement, what funcom did with the seemingly small venue like Atlantic Island Park and also with the extension of the story already teasered in „The Secret World“.What makes this game badThere are a couple things that could act as a road block. Casual players may find many aspects of the game unenjoyable. The lack of literally any gameplay other than walking through the park and exploring it's locations makes for a dull experience for people who want to kill and shoot things. Although being a horror game with minimal survival aspects – heart rate, blurred vision, smaller view – you will never truely feel threatened or fear for your survival. Everything is just atmosphere, and there is no killer stalking you or moments where you have to take immediate action to save yourself. Some may find that a lackluster experience. For it's price, the game also does not offer a very long experience, even with full exploration and all secrets the game just takes 2 hours to complete – and with very little arguments for replayability, that is of course not very much.Personal opinion and recommendationFor me, The Park was a fun experience and a good investment. I've played The Secret World, i'm a sucker for lore and story and i love the setting, so the game just strikes 10 with me. Even without former knowledge, you can enjoy The Park if you are into story driven experiences and if you really have the time to enjoy this game. What i mean by that is: Don't try to rush through the story. Don't try to play this game in an achievement hunt. If you don't give the narrative and the atmosphere a chance to grasp you, The Park won't be a good experience for you. Don't make the mistake of buying this game and expect something like Outlast or Amnesia, because The Park doesn't even want to be that type of game. Buy it expecting a movie, that focuses on introspective, creepy scenery and an increasingly disturbing tale of personal shortcomings, and you will have your fun with this game. I am biased towards The Park because of The Secret World and Funcom in general, so it has proven to be a good buy, even though i recommend waiting on a sale or holiday special to pick it up at a discount. Anyway: Give it a try if you're into it. It will give you little, but with that, won't disappoint you."
